pageContext.claim: “They don't ask him anything. They don't ask him whether or not he's corrupt. Are you corrupt. Hey, Sleepy Joe, are you corrupt? Remember, I asked him that question, and Chris Wallace of Fox wouldn't allow it. I said, 'Why? Why? Why won't you?' 'Well, I don't think it's appropriate to ask right now.' Chris Wallace.”
pageContext.analysis: This exchange only happened in Trump's head. During the first presidential debate, Trump never raised whether Biden was "corrupt" and Wallace never stopped him by saying the question was not appropriate.
